{# meta-data — NoCloud datasource identity payload.

WHY: cloud-init's NoCloud datasource keys on instance-id to decide
whether to re-run "once-per-instance" modules. We use the asset_tag
(stable across reimages) so re-imaging a host runs the boot-strap
steps again, but a reboot does not.

WHY: local-hostname is what gets written to /etc/hostname and used as
the kernel hostname. We pass the FQDN; cloud-init's hostname module
splits the short name itself.
#}
instance-id: {{ asset_tag }}
local-hostname: {{ hostname }}
